        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>Four of the galaxies within the group have fluxes of 1-3 mJy at 850 microns and spatial extents of 1 to 5 arcseconds in the optical.  We propose to image these galaxies in band 7 for its commensurate wavelength and improved resolution over the longer wavelengths available.  To image the full galaxy group, we require 7 pointings with a sensitivity of 0.06mJy and resolution of half an arcsecond.  With this depth, we hope to detect the other three group members so that we can constrain their properties within our model.</prj:justificationText>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
